A 49-year-old man has died after the cattle lorry he was driving was involved in a collision with another lorry on the M74.
Police said the crash happened near Elvanfoot, in South Lanarkshire, at about 13:20 on Wednesday.
The 49-year-old driver was pronounced dead at the scene. The 45-year-old driver of the other lorry was not injured.
Police have appealed for witnesses to the crash.
